The Accounting department is panicking. They noticed that the total sales in our "Category Reports" are lower than the total sales in the "Bank Account.

SELECT 
    -- Replace NULLs with a readable label
    ISNULL(ps.Name, 'Uncategorized') AS SubcategoryName,
    -- Calculate total revenue for the category
    SUM(sod.LineTotal) AS TotalRevenue,
    -- Count how many items were sold in this category
    COUNT(sod.SalesOrderDetailID) AS NumberOfSales
FROM Sales.SalesOrderDetail AS sod
INNER JOIN Production.Product AS pp
    ON sod.ProductID = pp.ProductID
LEFT JOIN Production.ProductSubcategory AS ps
    ON pp.ProductSubcategoryID = ps.ProductSubcategoryID
GROUP BY ps.Name
ORDER BY TotalRevenue DESC;
